HackToLive.org/wiki/UNetbootin_-_Super_Ubuntu

LUBI.sourceforge.net and LaunchPad.net/unetbootin >>UNetbootin allows for the installation of Ubuntu, Fedora, Mandriva, OpenSuse, Arch Linux, or Debian to a real partition, so it's no different from a standard install, only it has the advantage that it needs no CD.

Elinux.org/Boot_Time >>This page has information about reducing boot-up time for a Linux system. This is of interest for many embedded developers, because for many products customers expect to be able to use them very soon after system startup.

Edit /etc/rc.local to change what services start during boot.
